<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1287,2034]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,216,1287,1313]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Note.</emphasis>
Conversations between Bruno Spinosa (
<collectionCode box="[710,795,1288,1314]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">DEUN</collectionCode>
) and Fabrizio Rigato (
<collectionCode box="[1073,1168,1288,1314]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">MSNM</collectionCode>
), as reported to Barry Bolton, have established that the 
<typeStatus box="[539,641,1328,1354]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[680,814,1328,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Asphinctopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis box="[680,814,1328,1353]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">A. silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be found in the Silvestri collection in Naples. Daniel Burckhardt (
<collectionCode box="[383,474,1368,1394]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/1d5a-4efs" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Basel" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">NHMB</collectionCode>
) informs us that the 
<taxonomicName box="[716,816,1368,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Asphinctopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis box="[716,816,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[825,927,1368,1394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">holotype</typeStatus>
has never been in the Santschi collection.
</paragraph>
